WEBVTT

01:58.381 --> 02:03.381
Subtitles by explosiveskull

02:22.441 --> 02:27.614
(CHATTING QUIETLY)

02:30.916 --> 02:32.752
That's my girl.

02:33.852 --> 02:36.452
Is that a fact, now?

02:36.454 --> 02:39.790
You havin' a good time?

02:39.792 --> 02:41.658
I was.

02:41.660 --> 02:43.596
I have a feeling that's
all over now.

02:48.466 --> 02:49.866
(PUNCH)

02:49.868 --> 02:50.867
(SCUFFLING)

02:50.869 --> 02:52.368
(GLASS SHATTERS)

02:52.370 --> 02:53.570
(GROANING)

02:53.572 --> 02:55.575
(FIGHTING)

03:03.614 --> 03:04.513
<i>Fuck!</i>

03:04.515 --> 03:05.717
<i>Fuck you!</i>

03:10.555 --> 03:16.295
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

03:25.571 --> 03:33.846
(PHONE RINGING)

03:40.651 --> 03:42.922
Hello?

03:49.894 --> 03:51.731
I'll be right there.

04:02.640 --> 04:05.509
I gotta go meet some guy.

04:05.511 --> 04:06.679
At this hour?

04:11.015 --> 04:12.452
Yeah.

04:18.857 --> 04:21.557
I had to let some of the boys go
on account of the fact

04:21.559 --> 04:24.494
that it's been so quiet
around here.

04:24.496 --> 04:26.463
Am I gonna have to rehire
'em?

04:26.465 --> 04:27.997
Why?

04:27.999 --> 04:30.836
I mean, if Saxon plans on
staying in town for a while.

04:33.172 --> 04:33.936
I don't know.

04:33.938 --> 04:36.609
(DOOR BUZZING)

05:11.008 --> 05:14.610
When'd you get back?

05:14.612 --> 05:15.881
Last night.

05:17.749 --> 05:19.482
Didn't waste a second catching
up on old times,

05:19.484 --> 05:20.884
did you?

05:20.886 --> 05:22.655
No, I guess I didn't.

05:28.025 --> 05:30.429
What're you doing here
while you're back?

05:36.535 --> 05:37.501
Look, you've been gone
a long time.

05:37.503 --> 05:39.604
There's been a lot of changes
around here.

05:40.605 --> 05:42.507
There's some things I need
to talk to you about.

05:43.575 --> 05:46.576
That can wait at least 'til
you're cleaned up, rested up.

05:46.578 --> 05:47.877
I'm about as clean as
I'm gonna get.

05:47.879 --> 05:48.845
(SIGHS)

05:48.847 --> 05:50.045
What do you wanna talk about?

05:50.047 --> 05:51.716
Lots of things.

05:53.619 --> 05:54.686
My mother?

05:58.590 --> 05:59.525
Our mother.

06:01.059 --> 06:01.924
So you know?

06:01.926 --> 06:03.496
Know what?

06:05.563 --> 06:06.662
That she's gone.

06:06.664 --> 06:08.532
She passed.

06:08.534 --> 06:10.470
Not in the way they say
she did.

06:12.671 --> 06:14.737
I didn't think the truth was
something you could handle.

06:14.739 --> 06:15.905
What truth is that?

06:15.907 --> 06:17.710
That our mother
killed herself.

06:21.679 --> 06:22.746
She left you.

06:22.748 --> 06:24.581
She left us.

06:24.583 --> 06:25.782
Now, this was three
years ago, Saxon.

06:25.784 --> 06:29.552
You don't think pop and me
obsessed over the hows and whys?

06:29.554 --> 06:30.953
You skipped town, you
skipped over your grief.

06:30.955 --> 06:32.825
I didn't skip anything.

06:42.568 --> 06:43.835
You need to call that guy.

06:45.837 --> 06:46.906
Why?

06:48.573 --> 06:50.109
Mom left you some money.

06:51.842 --> 06:53.610
Mom didn't have any money.

06:53.612 --> 06:55.578
There was an
insurance policy.

06:55.580 --> 06:56.780
Mom didn't have any insurance.

06:56.782 --> 06:59.114
Apparently she did.

06:59.116 --> 07:00.617
Oh yeah?

07:00.619 --> 07:02.718
Why didn't she tell anyone?

07:02.720 --> 07:04.687
You know mom.

07:04.689 --> 07:05.922
She was always private.

07:05.924 --> 07:07.592
(SPITS)

07:08.994 --> 07:10.595
Not with me.

07:13.631 --> 07:16.968
(CHUCKLES)

07:18.936 --> 07:20.770
Oh, Jesus, Saxon.

07:20.772 --> 07:22.672
You wanna know how much?

07:22.674 --> 07:24.943
How much money I made
off my mother's death? Nah.

07:26.612 --> 07:28.944
Look. She did this for us.

07:28.946 --> 07:29.812
To look out for us.

07:29.814 --> 07:31.213
To give us an opportunity.

07:31.215 --> 07:32.148
I took it.

07:32.150 --> 07:33.682
I did what she wanted.

07:33.684 --> 07:35.554
I made a life for myself.

07:37.054 --> 07:38.657
What's your plan?

07:38.957 --> 07:39.855
Just gonna lay low
for a while.

07:39.857 --> 07:42.158
You don't have the
best history for it.

07:42.160 --> 07:43.862
Things change.

07:56.040 --> 07:58.610
Anyway, we'd all be a lot
happier if you'd just...

07:59.076 --> 08:00.145
stay gone.

08:01.679 --> 08:03.648
Who's "we"?

08:04.215 --> 08:06.051
Me.

08:11.155 --> 08:14.160
(SOMBRE PIANO
MUSIC PLAYING)

08:21.198 --> 08:24.203
(SOMBRE PIANO
MUSIC PLAYING)

08:37.682 --> 08:39.214
You're some kind of beautiful.

08:39.216 --> 08:41.052
(STOPS PLAYING)

08:42.287 --> 08:44.690
Feeling a little dark?

08:48.192 --> 08:50.126
Where have you been?

08:50.128 --> 08:51.730
I called your work.

08:54.700 --> 08:56.699
I gotta go check out
the farm.

08:56.701 --> 08:59.135
I think someone might
be squatting there.

08:59.137 --> 09:00.102
You haven't been there
in years.

09:00.104 --> 09:02.108
Why would someone be
at your mother's farm?

09:04.209 --> 09:05.777
'Cause it's his mother, too.

09:08.913 --> 09:10.048
Saxon?

09:12.817 --> 09:15.785
Dean, you said "some guy".

09:15.787 --> 09:16.852
You called your brother
"some guy".

09:16.854 --> 09:19.723
He is some guy.

09:19.725 --> 09:21.757
The silent routine
on your brother

09:21.759 --> 09:24.761
is not gonna cut it this time.

09:24.763 --> 09:27.130
I wouldn't know where
to start.

09:27.132 --> 09:29.234
How about from
the beginning?

09:33.739 --> 09:36.042
I think this is
the beginning.

11:14.873 --> 11:17.006
Long time.

11:17.008 --> 11:18.373
Miss the place?

11:18.375 --> 11:20.175
Not even a little bit.

11:20.177 --> 11:21.379
Yeah, not much has changed.

11:24.081 --> 11:26.181
Nothing ever changes.

11:26.183 --> 11:28.117
Not in this town.

11:28.119 --> 11:31.087
It was your brother.

11:31.089 --> 11:32.121
You know, I didn't wanna
say anything

11:32.123 --> 11:33.323
while you were on the inside,

11:33.325 --> 11:34.891
I know how you feel
about him,

11:34.893 --> 11:36.092
you don't need
any agitations...

11:36.094 --> 11:38.962
Spit it out.

11:38.964 --> 11:42.401
Your big brother's become
a big deal in this little town.

11:45.870 --> 11:47.305
He's pretty much everywhere.

11:48.440 --> 11:50.305
Even bought that bit ol'
fancy house

11:50.307 --> 11:51.875
we used to throw rocks at.

11:51.877 --> 11:54.010
Remember that?

11:54.012 --> 11:55.944
Good for him.

11:55.946 --> 11:58.881
You uh, you wanna see him
in action, watch him strut,

11:58.883 --> 12:00.282
go down to the town hall
tonight.

12:00.284 --> 12:01.117
He'll be there.

12:01.119 --> 12:03.122
Dean's a maneuverer.

12:03.922 --> 12:06.024
Born with a horseshoe
in his ass.

12:08.493 --> 12:10.425
Yeah, you're just about dumb
enough to believe in luck,

12:10.427 --> 12:12.263
aren't you?

12:20.171 --> 12:22.273
Why the hell'd you ever
come back, Saxon?

12:30.481 --> 12:32.317
I got questions in me.

12:34.319 --> 12:36.155
They keep me awake.

12:39.291 --> 12:41.223
A ton of questions.

12:41.225 --> 12:44.395
(FADING) I can't sleep until
they're not questions anymore.

12:46.431 --> 12:48.100
I'm haunted.

12:51.936 --> 12:53.471
I wanna be un-haunted.

12:59.244 --> 13:06.085
(APPLAUSE)

13:08.452 --> 13:09.484
Thank you, everybody.

13:09.486 --> 13:11.487
Thank you, thank you.

13:11.489 --> 13:15.992
When this man... and you
all know who this man is...

13:15.994 --> 13:17.526
when this man had the idea
to bring a prison

13:17.528 --> 13:21.197
to this sleepy little
town of ours

13:21.199 --> 13:24.299
you all thought he was crazy.

13:24.301 --> 13:28.237
Everybody was against it,
including me.

13:28.239 --> 13:32.541
Well, nobody thinks he's
crazy now.

13:32.543 --> 13:36.979
Gamble by name,
gamble by nature.

13:36.981 --> 13:38.982
Ladies and gentlemen,
Mr. Dean Gamble.

13:38.984 --> 13:42.988
(APPLAUSE)

13:49.259 --> 13:50.559
Uh, thank you.

13:50.561 --> 13:52.194
<i>My first...</i>

13:52.196 --> 13:54.399
<i>(SPEECH CONTINUES
IN BACKGROUND)</i>

14:03.273 --> 14:05.244
You must be Saxon.

14:08.278 --> 14:10.179
I'm Amelia.

14:10.181 --> 14:12.084
Dean's fiancÃ©.

14:15.286 --> 14:17.120
I've heard almost
nothing about you.

14:17.122 --> 14:19.021
The nothing's all good,
I hope.

14:19.023 --> 14:20.256
No, it's just you're...

14:20.258 --> 14:22.427
you're nothing like Dean's
impression of you.

14:24.162 --> 14:25.227
What a shame.

14:25.229 --> 14:27.566
I try to live my life by Dean's
impressions of me.

14:32.570 --> 14:33.202
You know, I'm...

14:33.204 --> 14:35.574
I'm from out of town, too.

14:37.307 --> 14:40.043
I guess we're kindred spirits.

14:40.045 --> 14:41.644
I like it here.

14:41.646 --> 14:44.579
It's... it's different.

14:44.581 --> 14:45.515
Is it?

14:45.517 --> 14:48.184
People are nicer, too.

14:48.186 --> 14:49.051
Are they?

14:49.053 --> 14:51.187
I think so.

14:51.189 --> 14:54.026
Well, don't believe everything
you think.

14:57.461 --> 14:59.197
So what do you do?

15:00.065 --> 15:01.467
Why?

15:03.067 --> 15:05.203
Because it's a good way
to get to know someone?

15:06.336 --> 15:07.636
What do you do?

15:07.638 --> 15:10.205
I was a teacher once.

15:10.207 --> 15:12.110
And now you're nothing.

15:13.210 --> 15:14.209
I wouldn't put it like that.

15:14.211 --> 15:16.414
How would you put it?

15:20.685 --> 15:23.185
Anyway, what I do is
my business.

15:23.187 --> 15:24.386
I was just being friendly.

15:24.388 --> 15:26.457
Now we're gonna
be friends now?

15:27.358 --> 15:29.257
I hope so.

15:29.259 --> 15:33.396
A friend of my enemy
is my enemy.

15:33.398 --> 15:36.335
Not quite how
the saying goes.

15:40.537 --> 15:42.306
Yes it is.

15:48.378 --> 15:51.380
<i>(SPEECH CONTINUES)</i>

15:51.382 --> 15:53.315
<i>...I want to thank you guys
all for coming</i>

15:53.317 --> 15:57.252
<i>and my father for
being here, and thank you...</i>

15:57.254 --> 16:02.393
(APPLAUSE)

16:08.133 --> 16:10.232
So I met your brother.

16:10.234 --> 16:12.135
What?

16:12.137 --> 16:13.202
Where'd you meet him?

16:13.204 --> 16:15.304
Tonight.

16:15.306 --> 16:17.640
You didn't... you didn't
invite him?

16:17.642 --> 16:19.210
God no.

16:22.312 --> 16:24.447
You know, I gotta tell you,

16:24.449 --> 16:27.349
he's not the wild animal
that you described.

16:27.351 --> 16:30.152
Don't be fooled by the gentle
nature of my brother.

16:30.154 --> 16:32.554
He's like a sleeping bear.

16:32.556 --> 16:36.192
Harmless 'til you poke
him with a stick.

16:36.194 --> 16:37.059
Listen to me.

16:37.061 --> 16:40.163
I need you to stay away
from him, ok?

16:40.165 --> 16:40.729
<i>Oh?</i>

16:40.731 --> 16:42.298
<i>Why?</i>

16:42.300 --> 16:43.165
<i>Hmm?</i>

16:43.167 --> 16:44.299
<i>Is he the big bad wolf?</i>

16:44.301 --> 16:46.537
Yeah, he's a big bad wolf.

17:15.733 --> 17:16.531
(BANGS CABINET)

17:16.532 --> 17:18.568
Shit.

17:18.569 --> 17:19.534
(KICKS CABINET)

17:19.536 --> 17:20.636
Fuck!

17:20.637 --> 17:22.570
FUCK!

17:22.573 --> 17:27.145
(BASHES DESK)

18:33.578 --> 18:36.348
(MOTORCYCLE ENGINE ROARS)

19:03.640 --> 19:04.706
(WHISTLES)

19:04.708 --> 19:06.344
Jack.

19:07.611 --> 19:09.811
Never seen you in here
without cuffs on.

19:09.813 --> 19:11.379
Can we talk?

19:11.381 --> 19:12.516
Talk?

19:13.451 --> 19:16.321
Well, ain't this day
just full of surprises?

19:17.455 --> 19:19.722
Who's in charge of
my mother's case?

19:19.724 --> 19:20.822
Case?

19:20.824 --> 19:22.357
What case?

19:22.359 --> 19:23.526
You mother committed
suicide,

19:23.528 --> 19:24.592
found some notes at her place.

19:24.594 --> 19:25.627
Why has nobody investigated?

19:25.629 --> 19:27.530
Investigated what?

19:27.532 --> 19:29.365
Your mother swallowed
a bottle of pills.

19:29.367 --> 19:30.433
No mystery.

19:30.435 --> 19:32.600
Not a happy woman,
reached her limit, checks out.

19:32.602 --> 19:33.868
How do you know
she was unhappy?

19:33.870 --> 19:35.070
Wasn't she?

19:35.072 --> 19:35.870
Yeah?

19:35.872 --> 19:36.705
Well, how do you know?

19:36.707 --> 19:38.574
Lucky guess, I guess.

19:38.576 --> 19:42.345
Money troubles,
messy divorce,

19:42.347 --> 19:44.347
son in and out of prison,
take your pick.

19:44.349 --> 19:45.714
Yeah, but no suspects?

19:45.716 --> 19:47.349
Of course we don't have
any suspects

19:47.351 --> 19:50.386
in your mother's suicide,
it's suicide.

19:50.388 --> 19:52.323
What about Dean?

19:56.627 --> 19:57.863
What?

19:58.628 --> 19:59.928
Come again?

19:59.930 --> 20:02.397
Dean.

20:02.399 --> 20:04.567
Boy.

20:04.569 --> 20:08.404
You really do have a hard on
for him, don't you?

20:08.406 --> 20:10.973
I wasn't sure how deep
it went.

20:10.975 --> 20:13.541
You really do hate him.

20:13.543 --> 20:15.877
Facts is facts, Jack.

20:15.879 --> 20:17.780
There ain't no facts
in your head, boy.

20:17.782 --> 20:19.447
I ain't your boy.

20:19.449 --> 20:21.483
Thank god.

20:21.485 --> 20:22.484
You like facts?

20:22.486 --> 20:24.653
Your mother didn't have
an enemy in this world.

20:24.655 --> 20:27.389
No sign of forced entry,
doors locked

20:27.391 --> 20:28.723
from the inside,
no prints.

20:28.725 --> 20:30.725
The scene didn't reveal
anything that said

20:30.727 --> 20:32.461
she didn't kill herself.

20:32.463 --> 20:36.531
No foul play, no weapons,
no nothing.

20:36.533 --> 20:37.567
No note.

20:37.569 --> 20:38.934
So? It wouldn't be the first
suicide in history

20:38.936 --> 20:39.934
without a note...

20:39.936 --> 20:40.501
Listen, our mother wouldn't go
to the bathroom

20:40.503 --> 20:42.907
without leaving a note.

20:44.942 --> 20:46.008
This is a waste of my time.

20:46.010 --> 20:48.543
Yeah, why don't you go back
to your movie, Jack?

20:48.545 --> 20:50.913
Look, asshole.

20:50.915 --> 20:54.683
You got something from
reality you wanna share with me?

20:54.685 --> 20:56.620
Otherwise, fuck off.

21:05.163 --> 21:05.961
Congratulations.

21:05.963 --> 21:07.029
A business license.

21:07.031 --> 21:08.830
Two weeks before she died.

21:08.832 --> 21:09.799
She's starting a business.

21:09.801 --> 21:10.933
Does that look like the actions
of somebody

21:10.935 --> 21:12.704
who's checking out?

21:15.439 --> 21:17.839
Look, son, you're reaching.

21:17.841 --> 21:19.841
I know it's tough.

21:19.843 --> 21:23.979
I know it's hit you hard,
harder than anyone.

21:23.981 --> 21:27.715
Why can't you just accept
the truth?

21:27.717 --> 21:29.851
Your mother was tired.

21:29.853 --> 21:31.655
She wanted out.

21:34.992 --> 21:36.861
'Cause I knew her.

21:58.483 --> 22:04.556
(GRUNTS)

22:22.005 --> 22:29.979
<i>We are a species with almost
dumbfounding kindness.</i>

22:29.981 --> 22:34.782
We romance each other,
we nurse one another,

22:34.784 --> 22:40.055
weep for each other, and ever
since science taught us how,

22:40.057 --> 22:45.728
we willingly tear the very
organs from our bodies

22:45.730 --> 22:48.763
and give them to each other.

22:48.765 --> 22:54.869
And at the same time
we slaughter each other.

22:54.871 --> 23:02.578
The savage and the sweet
can exist in any one animal.

23:02.580 --> 23:06.147
They can exist
in any one person,

23:06.149 --> 23:10.051
and often in one instant.

23:10.053 --> 23:14.088
A good man can do
a bad thing

23:14.090 --> 23:17.529
and a bad man can do
a good thing.

23:20.031 --> 23:22.100
So what does that make them?

23:25.969 --> 23:28.672
What makes a man good?

23:55.866 --> 23:58.637
<i>Nice costume, Leonard.</i>

24:01.772 --> 24:04.842
Why didn't anybody tell me
about the money?

24:10.947 --> 24:13.618
That's all you have to say?

24:15.719 --> 24:17.853
After all the time
you've been gone?

24:17.855 --> 24:21.022
I didn't come here
to shoot the breeze.

24:21.024 --> 24:24.193
I didn't tell you 'cause
I didn't know.

24:24.195 --> 24:26.998
I found out a few days
after the funeral,

24:29.867 --> 24:32.070
when you would have found out.

24:32.969 --> 24:34.738
If you were around.

24:36.640 --> 24:37.673
Where you been?

24:37.675 --> 24:39.107
You don't think
that's strange?

24:39.109 --> 24:41.743
She wouldn't tell you,
not her kids, not a soul?

24:41.745 --> 24:43.811
Your mother didn't tell me
much in the end.

24:43.813 --> 24:45.215
Why would she?

24:47.651 --> 24:48.783
Come inside for a spell.

24:48.785 --> 24:49.784
Might do you some good.

24:49.786 --> 24:51.086
I've got tons to sort out.

24:51.088 --> 24:53.955
I don't think praying's
gonna help.

24:53.957 --> 24:56.791
I was thinking more along
the lines of confession.

24:56.793 --> 24:58.827
I'll pass.

24:58.829 --> 25:00.663
You don't believe in
God now?

25:00.665 --> 25:02.196
That's a whole new
kind of alone.

25:02.198 --> 25:04.799
I don't got no beef
with God.

25:04.801 --> 25:08.136
I don't go out of my way
to please him, either.

25:08.138 --> 25:10.007
Sounds like us.

25:11.908 --> 25:13.811
Not really.

25:21.185 --> 25:23.088
How did we end up like this?

25:23.954 --> 25:25.820
Like what?

25:25.822 --> 25:27.725
Strangers.

25:31.061 --> 25:32.830
I don't know.

25:33.697 --> 25:36.098
I figured when I was born
you decided I was the bad one

25:36.100 --> 25:37.133
and you never let it go.

25:37.135 --> 25:40.672
You didn't do much to change
my mind about it.

25:42.706 --> 25:45.139
You forget, Leonard.

25:45.141 --> 25:47.946
I knew you before you were
touched by God.

25:53.751 --> 25:56.253
They say time heals
all wounds,

25:59.724 --> 26:02.660
that it's never too late
to turn it all around.

26:11.334 --> 26:13.737
(CLOSES DOOR)

26:58.248 --> 26:59.781
Yes.

26:59.783 --> 27:01.983
Yes, yes, yes.

27:01.985 --> 27:04.054
Here it is.

27:08.292 --> 27:09.957
Ah.

27:09.959 --> 27:11.827
Now, if the client,
uh, commits suicide

27:11.829 --> 27:14.363
within the first two years a
beneficiary will not receive

27:14.365 --> 27:17.031
the face value
of the coverage.

27:17.033 --> 27:20.802
So you're very lucky that
the two years had lapsed

27:20.804 --> 27:23.238
before your mother,
uh... passed.

27:23.240 --> 27:24.873
In the fashion that she did.

